***Phishing is illegal and not promoted***
***This is purely for educational purposes. Do not recreate this on authentic websites even if you own them***

A. What are the various files in the folder:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. The index.html file has the cloned version of the original website (stored on Login.html). 
2. The index.html script redirects the login credentials to the creds.txt file by using the stealer.php file.
3. stealer.php contains the script to secretly copy the login credentials when the user enters them on the fake but identical site.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

B. How to use files for simulating attack:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Download the XAMPP application and run the apache module from the dashboard.
2. Download the phishing-demo folder and make sure it is stored in the XAMPP folder path, under htdocs folder.
3. Open a browser and copy paste URL: http://localhost/phishing-demo/index.html
4. This should bring us an exact replica of the original website. 
5. Enter the login credentials.
6. Open the creds.txt file and the credentials used for login will be recorded. 

This shows how an attacker can steal the login credentials through a phishing attack.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

